<HEADLINE> Rail Transport to Resume in Northern Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Rail transportation between the
capital Luanda and the city of Dondo, Kwanza-norte Province, will
resume in January next year after nine-month suspension, head of
the Luanda Railroad said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to Manuel Gourgel Rodrigues, four passenger trains
will shuttle along the newly repaired railway every week.
</P>
<P>
Rodrigues said that his department is trying to rehabilitate
the bridge over the Luinha River,185 kilometers from Luanda, to
prolong the railroad to Lucala, Kwanza-norte Province, considered
as doorway to the north and northeast Angola.
</P>
<P>
During the 25-year civil war, all the main railway networks
have been paralyzed due to the destructions of tracks and bridges
by the rebels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
