<HEADLINE> Israeli Settlement Policy Endangers Mideast Peace March: Egyptian FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
CAIRO, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Egypt on Tuesday warned of the
danger that Israel poses to the Middle East peace process by
continuing settlement expansion in the occupied territories.
</P>
<P>
Israel is continuing settlement activities in the occupied
Palestinian lands, a move which will be detrimental to the peace
talks between the Palestinians and Israel, Egyptian Foreign
Minister Amr Moussa told reporters after a meeting between Egyptian
 President Hosni Mubarak and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
Arafat arrived here earlier in the day for a short visit. He
focused his talks with Mubarak on Israel's settlement policy.
</P>
<P>
"The information aired by the Israeli side regarding halt to
its settlement activities totally contradicted with the reality,"
the Egyptian foreign minister said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat presented some data in this regard involving the fact
that the Israeli government had published tenders for the building
of 7,000 new housing units in the West Bank in addition to other
units in Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians have been angered and frustrated by Israel's
settlement expansion. Most of the international community considers
 the Israeli settlement activities as illegal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
