<HEADLINE> Iran Vows to Continue Efforts to Resolve Chechen Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Tuesday vowed to
continue its effort to resolve the Chechen crisis through
diplomatic means as Russian troops have reportedly captured parts
of the suburb of the Chechen capital of Grozny.
</P>
<P>
The second batch of Iran's humanitarian relief materials can be
sent to the Chechen refugees as soon as the Russian government
gives approval, Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi said.
</P>
<P>
Expressing regret over the continuation of the current crisis in
 Chechnya, he said that the Muslim world believes there should be a
 peaceful solution to the Chechen crisis.
</P>
<P>
Russian federal troops have controlled the northern suburb of
Grozny while reconnaissance units have stepped up their activities
inside the besieged city, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Some Russian military officers claimed that the Russian forces
would soon take over the city, the stronghold of Chechen rebels.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian minister underlined that the Chechen people are the
major victims of the crisis, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi also announced readiness of the Organization of the
Islamic Conference (OIC) to send another high-ranking delegation to
 the region in the near future to continue discussions on the
Chechen crisis.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, an OIC delegation led by Kharrazi visited
Moscow and Chechnya and discussed a possible political resolution
to the Chechen issue with Russian officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
