<HEADLINE> Macao Handover to Promote Mozambique-China Ties: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, December 14 (Xinhua) -- The handover of Macao to China
will help promote the Mozambican-Chinese relations, Mozambican
Foreign Minister Leonardo Simao said in a recent interview with
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that with Macao as a bridge, the relations between
Mozambique and China will surely be further promoted," said Simao
who paid a visit to Macao several years ago.
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that his country has had an honorary
consulate in Macao and the Chinese government has agreed to retain
it.
</P>
<P>
The traditional ties between the Portuguese-speaking southern
African country and Macao will be strengthened, Simao said.
</P>
<P>
Macao's return to China after being ruled by the Portuguese for
more than 150 years will offer more opportunities for the
cooperation between Mozambique and China, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
China and Portugal have set up a good example for the world by
resolving the issue of Macao through negotiations, Simao said.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the Taiwan issue will also be resolved
satisfactorily," the minister said, citing the peaceful return of
Hongkong to China through peaceful negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican minister will lead a delegation to Macao to
witness the handover later this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
