<HEADLINE> Iran Blasts Israel for Killing Hamas Activists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Ministry
spokesman Hamid Reza Asefi on Tuesday blasted Israel for "
assassinating" two activists of the Islamic Resistance Movement
(Hamas).
</P>
<P>
Asefi expressed Iran's anger at the killing of two Hamas
activists by Israeli security agents and termed the act as "a
blatant example of state terrorism," the Islamic Republic News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Israeli army announced on Tuesday that its undercover troops
were fired at while approaching a house in Beit Awwa village near
Hebron on the West Bank and the forces killed two Hamas activists
and arrested three others in a response shootout.
</P>
<P>
Israeli media said that one of the dead was identified as Iyad
Batat, a regional Hamas military commander.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian spokesman said that committing such crimes while
chanting slogans in favor of peace betrayed contradiction in
policies being pursued by the Israeli regime.
</P>
<P>
Resort to terrorism and support for state terrorism are rooted
in the Israeli nature, he said, adding that the Israeli regime is
still main factor of instability and insecurity in the region.
</P>
<P>
Iran refused to recognize Israel after the 1979 Islamic
revolution and voiced its opposition to the Middle East peace
process, but it has close ties with the anti-Israeli militant
groups, including Hamas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
