<HEADLINE> World's Largest Internet Cafe to be Opened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 14 (Xinhua) -- A world's largest Internet
cafe will be opened in March 2000 in Amsterdam, capital of the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The cafe, EasyEverything, a sister company of the airline
easyJet, will have 650 terminals. According to the EasyEverything
director Stelios Haji-Joannou, the computers in the cafe will be
superfast, and connection will be cheap.
</P>
<P>
In offpeak hours, surfers, e-mailers and chat-group junkies
will be able to connect up to the Web for less than they would be
able to through normal home phone lines, Haji-Joannou said.
</P>
<P>
EasyEverything opened its first Internet cafe in London earlier
this year. The Amsterdam webcafe will be opened 24 hours a day and
will be the prototype for three similar cafes around the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
In terms of its scale and the number of computing terminals, it
will be the largest Internet cafe so far in the world, the
authorities of Amsterdam said in a news release.
</P>
<P>
Amsterdam is the biggest city in the Kingdom of the Netherlands
with the population of 720,000. Foreign companies, international
organizations and 140 nationalities create a comsmopolitan
atmosphere. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
