<HEADLINE> Nearly 700 Kilograms of Hashish Seized in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Greek customs officials seized
674 kilograms of hashish from a truck driven by an Albanian early
Tuesday at the border station of Kristallopigi in Florina.
</P>
<P>
The 38-year-old Albanian driver, Jemal Kouka, was arrested
after customs officials discovered the hashish packed in 380
packages concealed in a hidden compartment of his refrigerator
truck, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The driver told the inspectors that an Albanian had given him
the hashish to transport to the northern Greek city of
Thessaloniki. He was to be given the address for delivery by
mobile phone when he was near the city. 
</P>
