<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt to Host COMESA Summit: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Egypt will for the first time
host a summit of the Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa
(COMESA) at the end of next February, a visiting senior Egyptian
official said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Reda Bebars, ambassador in the Cabinet of the Foreign Minister
of the Egyptian Government, said that the aim of the conference is
to increase awareness of the international business community on
the COMESA as an emerging economic bloc that has a stable
predictable trade and investment regime.
</P>
<P>
Bebars and his delegation arrived here Monday for a three-day
visit to consult the Zambian government and the COMESA Secretariat
over the meeting to be held on February 28-29, 2000.
</P>
<P>
The conference with the theme of "COMESA 2000: the Emerging
Market" will also contribute to the identification and promotion
of investment opportunities in the COMESA region as well as
enhance intra-COMESA trade and economic relations, according to a
COMESA press release issued here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The summit is expected to contribute to the realization of a
COMESA free trade area due to start in October 2000.
</P>
<P>
The conference will discuss among other things, construction,
oil gas and petrochemicals, mining and minerals, banking and
financial services, capital markets, agriculture and
agro-business, manufacturing, tourism and information technology.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to attract over 1,000 delegates including
ministers from COMESA member countries, chief executive officers
of multi-national and regional companies, as well as
representatives of international cooperating partners.
</P>
<P>
The exports of Egypt to other COMESA members doubled after its
entry to the regional group last February.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's intra-COMESA trade hit 106.5 million U.S. dollars in
the first half of this year compared with 78.2 million dollars in
the same period of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
