<HEADLINE> Switzerland Freezes Abacha Accounts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland has frozen more
than half a billion dollars in bank accounts related to the late
Nigerian dictator, Sani Abacha, according to Swiss Radio
International Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The authorities ordered a provisional block on any accounts in
the name of Abacha, his family and associates, the Swiss radio
said.
</P>
<P>
It quoted a Swiss lawyer representing the Nigerian government
as saying, "There's no doubt that the Swiss authorities are going
to further confiscate in favor of the Nigerian government and
remit the funds to Nigeria."
</P>
<P>
"It is to the persons involved to prove that the money they
have comes from legitimate sources. It would be very difficult for
these people to prove that," he added.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria suspects the former military regime of systematic
corruption and embezzlement. It has asked Switzerland for help in
its investigation two months ago, and has until the middle of
January to make a formal request for legal assistance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
