<HEADLINE> Greek Banks Ready to Deal With Millennium Bug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 14 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Greek Banks
said Tuesday that all its members were year 2000 compliant and
ready to tackle the changeover in dates to the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Tuesday, the association said that it had
been working on the millennium bug for the past three years and
had coordinated efforts with the Bank of Greece, the country's
central bank.
</P>
<P>
The association said that clients' accounts would suffer no
effects and transactions would proceed normally.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Greek electronic experts warned Tuesday that many
Greeks firms were expected to encounter serious difficulties with
VAT calculations and dates on their receipts due to the millennium
bug as there was no time for some 300,000 old cash registers to be
replaced by the end of the year with machines impervious to the
problem. 
