<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Suspends Vasile's Positions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Just hours after Radu Vasile
was forced to quit from his premiership, his party decided on
Tuesday to suspend all party positions he has held and ban him
from being elected into the party leadership within two years.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Christian Democrat National Peasant' Party
of Romania (CDNPPR), said the decision was made according to
Vasile's performance since Vasile became Romanian premier April
1998, and especially during the current government crisis.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, Romanian President Emil Constantinescu and
ruling coalition partners announced the dismissal of Vasile as
premier after his party withdrew support and most ministers
resigned.
</P>
<P>
"He (Vasile) is unable to fulfill his duties since the majority
of his cabinet members have resigned, which means the government
is unable to function." Constantinescu's spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
But Vasile said the president's action was "unconstitutional"
and vowed to bring the case to the court of appeal.
</P>
<P>
Vasile had been the general secretary of the CDNPPR before he
was named by his party as premier candidate. Under the party's
constitution, he can immediately resume his post in the party
after he relinquishes his premiership.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Vasile was choosing from his party
candidates to fill the vacancies left over by the ministers have
resigned.
</P>
<P>
Vasile is still supported by roughly half of the party members
and youth wing of the party.
</P>
<P>
In the meanwhile, many Romanian opposition parties, including
the Social Democracy Party of Romania, believed that the
president's dismissal of Vasile has violated the Constitution and
may plunge the country into political chaos.
</P>
<P>
The opposition Greater Romania Party has started to collect
signatures for ousting the president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
