<HEADLINE> Canada-EU Summit to Open in Ottawa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Canada will discuss trade and
investment issues with the European Union (EU) at a summit meeting
to open here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The semi-annual summit will be devoted to "growing trade and
investment ties" and in other areas of "close working relationship
", Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien said Tuesday in a news
release.
</P>
<P>
Attending the summit will be Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari,
who is also current President of European Council, Finnish Prime
Minister Paavo Lipponen and President of the European Commission
Romano Prodi, according to the release.
</P>
<P>
Other issues on the agenda will include discussions on an
international framework to facilitate electronic commerce,
northern cooperation and proliferation of small arms. 
</P>
