<HEADLINE> U.S. Warns Taliban on bin Laden's Possible Actions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States has
warned Afghanistan's Taliban movement that it would be responsible
for any terrorist actions taken by Saudi-born exile Osama bin
Laden, White House spokesman Joe Lockhart said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The head of the counter terrorism unit at the State (
Department) ... met with Taliban yesterday and delivered a message
that any terrorist activities by bin Laden group we would hold
Taliban responsible for," Lockhart told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"We wanted to make sure they understood that their support in
harboring the bin Laden organization was noted here in the United
States and any activity ...we would hold them responsible for," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The United States issued a worldwide caution on Saturday to its
citizens traveling abroad through the start of the New Year and
Ramadan, citing "credible information that terrorists are planning
attacks" against them.
</P>
<P>
"I can tell you that recently there were some suspects arrested
and we believe they belong to the bin Laden organization and were
planning terrorist attacks," Lockhart said.
</P>
<P>
He did not say where the people were arrested, saying the
United State's "effort to combat terrorism" was continuing.
</P>
