<HEADLINE> Egypt to Stage Antiquities Exhibition in Japan to Mark Cradles of Civilizations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
CAIRO, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Egypt has decided to stage an
exhibition of antiquities in Japan next year as part of the
celebrations organized by Japan to mark the "cradles of
civilizations," the top Egyptian antiquities official said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition due to be held next August is designed to
showcase the greatness of Egypt's ancient civilization, said
Gaballah Ali Gaballah, secretary general of the Egyptian Higher
Council of Antiquities.
</P>
<P>
It will display about 100 pieces of antiquities dating back to
various eras of ancient Egypt, along with a selected collection of
ancient pieces reflecting the civilizations of China and India,
Gaballah was quoted by Egypt's official Middle East News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Higher Council of Antiquities took the decision
during a recent meeting with Minister of Culture Farouq Hosni, the
official added.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition also comes as part of Japan's celebrations to
mark the advent of the new millennium and falls within the
framework of Egypt's contribution to the world activities in this
regard, Gaballah said.
</P>
<P>
Egypt will first display its antiquities in the Japanese
capital of Tokyo and later in some other cities for several months,
 he added.
</P>
<P>
He expected that the antiquities exhibition will offer an
important opportunity to boost the Japanese interest in visiting
Egypt and give a momentum to the development of the Egyptian
tourism industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
