<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO,, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Chilean Justice Minister
Soledad Alvear Tuesday resigned to join the left-wing presidential
candidate Ricardo Lagos for the runoff on January 16.
</P>
<P>
"The decision I have taken today is transcendental. As a woman,
a democrat and a Christian, I consider a duty to work in the
campaign of Ricardo Lagos with the purpose of having a third
Concertacion government," said the minister.
</P>
<P>
She announced that Justice vice minister Jose Antonio Gomez
will assume as minister, during the three remaining months of the
present government.
</P>
<P>
Lagos and wight-win populist Jaquin Lavin will campaign ahead
of the January 16 second-round vote to decide who will lead the
South American country's 15 million people.
</P>
<P>
Lagos of the ceter-left ruling Concertation coalition won on
Sunday the slimmest of victories over Lavin. No one got 50 percent
of the votes in the first round of voting.
</P>
<P>
It is thought that the former Justice minister participation in
the campaign of Lagos, whose majority was obtained in the first
round of voting, is aimed at getting the vote of women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
