<HEADLINE> French Parliament Presents Report on Kosovo War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Defense Commission of the
French National Assembly presented a report on the Kosovo War
Wednesday after making a study on the cause of the war.
</P>
<P>
The report, presented by defense commission chairman Socialist
deputy Paul Quiles, said that the "intransigence" of the Yugoslav
authorities on Kosovo made it necessary for NATO to intervene.
</P>
<P>
It said that the "diplomatic effort" launched by the Western
countries since 1997 for solving the Kosovo crisis was "constant,
sincere and resolved."
</P>
<P>
The report, written by a team of French parliament deputies
headed by Socialist Francois Lamy, was adopted by all deputies at
the National Assembly except a Communist deputy.
</P>
<P>
"The failure of the talks (in Rambouillet), attributable to the
Serb intransigence, led inevitably to the confrontation," it said.
</P>
<P>
The deputies also regretted that NATO announced at the
beginning of the conflict that it would exclude a ground
intervention.
</P>
<P>
"NATO should have kept a certain ambiguity on its strategic
choices," it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
