<HEADLINE> First Passat Car Rolls Off Production Line in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The first Passat sedan rolled
off the assembly line today at Shanghai Volkswagen, China's
leading car producer.
</P>
<P>
The Passat is modeled after Passat B5 and has a maximum speed
of 206 km per hour. The car can travel approximately 100
kilometers on only 5.8 liters of gasoline, said Hong Jiming,
general manager of the company.
</P>
<P>
