<HEADLINE> UAE Lifts Ban on Cow Import From Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates on
Wednesday lifted a ban on the import of cows and cow products from
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The ban has been in effect since 1993 because of fear of bovine
plague disease in Pakistani cows, the official WAM news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The ban was lifted according to an order issued by Saeed
Mohammad al-Ragabani, minister of agriculture and fisheries.
</P>
<P>
The order was based on information from the Paris-based
International Office on Epidemics that Pakistan is free of bovine
plague disease, WAM said. 
