<HEADLINE> UN Experts on Beijing's Development Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The UN experts said that Beijing is playing an important role
in the global circulation of cash and technology, attracting about
160 major multinational corporations and 300 large international
financial companies.
</P>
<P>
The output value of service industry in major international
cities around the world accounts for at least 70 percent of the
total gross domestic product (GDP). The experts pointed out the
output value of Hong Kong's service industry accounts for 82
percent of its GDP, adding that Beijing still has a long way to go.
</P>
<P>
The total output value of Beijing's service industry reached
100 billion yuan (about 12 billion U.S. dollars) last year,
accounting for 56.3 percent of its GDP, said Zhang Mao, deputy
mayor of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The experts advised the Beijing municipal government to
encourage competition and adopt favorable policies to accelerate
growth of service industry.
</P>
<P>
They said that Beijing is not only the political and cultural
center of China, but also the center of information and technology
with vast human resources necessary for developing its service
industry. 
</P>
