tolerate armed assaults and condemned the attack launched by the
rebel New People's Army (NPA) on a police headquarters in Danao,
Bohol province, resulting in the death of two cops.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine government called off offensive operations
against the NPA from December 10 to January 9, 2000 in observance
of the Christmas season.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the NPA also declared holiday cease-fire from
December 22 to December 25 and from December 30 to January 2, 2000.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Estrada reminded the military in Mindanao to respect
the traditional period of Ramadan observed by the MILF, but
stressed that violations of an existing cease-fire should not be
tolerated and that the people should be protected from any
aggression. 
