<HEADLINE> Shares Prices Sink on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices maintained a
downward trend on Singapore Stock Market Wednesday as investors
continued to take profits on blue chips.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Time Index (STI) closed 39.83 points
lower to end at 2,329.42 points.
</P>
<P>
Total volume was 208.08 million units valued at 627.57 million
Singapore dollars (373.55 million U.S. dollars). Losers
outnumbered gainers by 277 to 41 with 151 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was the 16.39 million parcel by PacCent which
was transacted at 10.80 Singapore dollars per share. It was
followed by AFP which had 15.26 million shares done. SingTel was
the next with 8.93 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH 100 led gainers of the day moving up 40 cents to close at
33.70 Singapore dollars. Global gained 30 cents to finish at 8.30
Singapore dollars. Asean picked up 20 cents to end at 9.60 U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser of the day
plunging by 130 cents to close at 30.60 Singapore dollars. PacCent
sank 70 cents to finish at 10.80 Singapore dollars. DBS retreated
50 cents to end at 25.60 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that many fund managers had closed their doors and
were taking off for their year-end holidays.
</P>
<P>
They said sentiment was also dampened by weaker U.S. and
regional markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
