<HEADLINE> Macao to Issue New Banknote on First Day of Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Macao will issue new banknote on
December 20 -- the first day it returns to the motherland,
announced the Monetary and Cambial Authority of Macao (MCAM).
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the MCAM Anselmo Teng told a press conference here
today that the new banknote is issued to mark Macao's return to
the motherland, and the issuing date on the notes has been
accordingly changed to December 20, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Another change on the face of the notes is the new signatures
of current general managers of the Macao Branch of the Bank of
China (BOC) and the Macao Branch of the Banco Nacional Ultramarino
(BNU), the two note-issuing banks in Macao.
</P>
<P>
The total face value of the new issuance will be 2.26 billion
Patacas, of which 1.31 billion will be issued by the BOC and 950
million by the BNU, Teng said.
</P>
<P>
The new notes include face values of 20 Patacas, 50 Patacas,
100 Patacas, 500 Patacas and 1,000 Patacas, which will circulate
together with the existing notes, he added.
</P>
<P>
With the new issuance, the total cash volume of the Macao
Patacas has exceeded 6.8 billion, which is sufficient to meet
resident's needs.
</P>
<P>
General Manager of the BOC Macao Branch Zhu Chi said that his
bank has completed all the necessary preparations for issuing the
new banknote, and will begin to supply the new notes from December
20.
</P>
<P>
"Joining in the new issuance in Macao reflects BOC's full
confidence in Macao's social and economic development prospects
and BOC's active commitment to protecting Macao's economic and
financial stability and development," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
