<HEADLINE> Japan's Extra Parliament Session Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Japan's 146th extraordinary Diet
(parliament) session ended Wednesday after enacting dozens of
bills, including legislation to help the country's small
businesses, and to crack down on the AUM Shinri Kyo cult.
</P>
<P>
During the 48-day session, a total of 88 bills proposed by the
Japanese government and individual lawmakers were enacted.
</P>
<P>
A bill to reduce 20 of the 200 proportional representation
seats in the 500-seat House of Representatives (lower house) was
not enacted and was passed over to the regular Diet session, which
convenes in January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
