<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Seven people, including a
 seven- year-old girl, died instantly when two minibus taxis
collided in Durban, South Africa, on Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
KwaZulu-Natal Road Traffic Inspectorate spokesman Vijen Murugan
said they were not sure how many people were injured at this stage
but said the figure could be high as 20.
</P>
<P>
Murugan said it appeared that two fully-laden minibus taxis
were travelling to Durban at 10 a.m. when one lost control and
crashed into the side of the other.
</P>
<P>
Both taxis overturned and were badly damaged. The highway
would be closed for several hours while investigators determined
the cause of the accident, the South African Press Association
reported.
</P>
<P>
Murugan said provincial transport officials flew to the scene
and was shocked by what they saw.  
