<HEADLINE> Bangkok Bank Invests in E-business Banking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Bangkok Bank PLC, Thailand's
largest commercial bank, announced Wednesday it will install IBM
mainframes, a state-of-art storage system and an integrated call
center to offer 24-hour e-business for customers.
</P>
<P>
Chartsiri Sophonpanich, president of the bank, said the new
investments are part of the bank's global vision for banking in
the new millennium, according to a press release of the bank.
</P>
<P>
"We want Bangkok Bank's customers to have the opportunity to
bank anytime, from anywhere by means they are most comfortable
with," he said.
</P>
<P>
The bank need to be "responsive to change, capable of operating
around the clock and truly global" in an environment where new
products and services are announced every day, Chartsiri said.
</P>
<P>
To meet these objectives, the very first thing the bank has to
do is to put in place a robust, comprehensive information
technology infrastructure which will enable their business
strategy, he added.
</P>
<P>
Based on the enterprise storage server which is an all-
inclusive storage solution available for the banking and finance
industries, the new service will offer real-time responses from
customer service representatives, who are on call at all times.
</P>
<P>
The benefits of the new phone banking center are not just those
of reducing costs and staff but rather gained from increased
levels of customer satisfaction and customer service staff no
longer have to be stationed at every branch, the press release
said.
</P>
<P>
The bank claims the system is the largest installment of its
kind in the Asia Pacific region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
