between South African and Rwandan governments.
</P>
<P>
Zuma's spokesman Khangelani Hlongwane told reporters on
Wednesday that the minister would be joined by Minister of
Agriculture Thoko Didiza, Director-General of Agriculture Bongiwe
Njobe and officials from her department.
</P>
<P>
Zuma will leave Rwanda on Friday to attend the Conference on
Security, Stability, Development and Co-operation in Africa
(CSSDCA) to be held in Arusha, Tanzania over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
