by foreign ministers from across Africa, Hlongwane said.
</P>
<P>
He said the steering committee would deliberate on re-launching
the CSSDCA within the framework of the Algiers and Sirte
Declarations, which emphasized the need to maintain peace,
security and economic development within Africa.
</P>
<P>
He said they would also review the Kampala document -- a
revised initiative designed to complement the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) in critical areas, mainly conflict
prevention, management and resolution.
</P>
<P>
The document also stresses the need for economic integration
within Africa.
</P>
<P>
Apart from these meetings, Zuma was also expected to discuss
the situation in the Democratic Republic of the Congo following
negative reports on the alleged violations of the Lusaka peace
deal. 
