Ahmed said the government is actively considering to reintroduce
25 percent cash incentives on export of weaving products to
encourage and nurture the traditional weaving industry.
</P>
<P>
The government will extend all-out cooperation to the nearly
100,000 weavers in the country for quality weaving products to
boost export, he said.
</P>
<P>
He called upon the weavers to be united under one umbrella for
reaping benefits of the incentives, urging entrepreneurs, fashion
designers and concerned persons to popularize the weavers'
products in international markets.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Sarwar Hossain, president of the Weaving Products
Manufacturers Business Association, urged the government to allow
the weavers duty-free import of color and cotton for making the
weaving products competitive and demanded for establishing a
weaving bank for ensuring easy soft loans for the weavers.
