overcame a weak opening to post a slight gain Wednesday, pushed
higher by the performance of key blue chips.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 10.9 points higher to close at
3119.0, after hitting a low of 3100.8.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index closed up 16.5 points to 5417.4 and
the all resources index moved up 7.6 points to 1310.6.
</P>
<P>
In the banking sector the two biggest banks made small gains.
The National Australia Bank picked up five cents to 22.97
Australian dollars and the Commonwealth Bank edged up 0.7 of a
cent to 25.51 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Westpac slipped back four cents to 10.66 Australian dollars and
ANZ lost four cents to 11.48 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The national turnover was a volume of 607.13 million shares
worth 1.62 billion Australian dollars (1.07 billion U.S. dollars).
There were 651 rising stocks, 694 falling and 518 were steady.
</P>
</TEXT>
