<HEADLINE> Two Murders on French Trains Seem to Be Work of One Man </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Two murders which took place on
two trains in France recently could be committed by one same man,
as the photofits established in the two murders correspond to a
same man, Agence France-Presse quoted judicial sources as saying
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Policemen investigating the murder of a British student Isabel
Peake, who was killed in a train from Limoge in central France to
Paris on the night of October 12, will check information with
their colleagues working on the murder of Corinne Caillaux, who
was killed Tuesday night in a train from Calais to Vintimille.
</P>
<P>
The body of Peake was found along a railway in Chabenet in the
province of Indre, central France, on October 13.
</P>
<P>
Caillaux, 36, who was traveling with her five-year-old son, was
found killed with knife in the restroom of a sleeping wagon when
the train was having a stop in Dijon, eastern France Tuesday night.
</P>
</TEXT>
