<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank of Greece Cuts Intervention Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Greece, the
country's central bank, announced a 0.75 percent cut in its 14-day
deposit rate as part of the plan to bring Greek interest rates
into parity with the rest of the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
After a meeting of the Monetary Policy Council on Wednesday,
the central bank reduced its intervention rate from the present 11.
5 percent to 10.75 percent.
</P>
<P>
The bank slashed the primary overnight lending rate by 10.25
percent from 11 percent, and the secondary rate from 9.25 percent
to 9 percent.
</P>
<P>
It further cut the lombard rate from 13 percent to 12.25
percent.
</P>
<P>
This is the second such reduction in just under two months. On
October 21, the bank reduced its basic intervention rate by 0.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's rate cut may be followed by another in February,
the size of which will depend on the macroeconomic environment at
that point in time.
</P>
<P>
Greece's commercial banks are expected to follow in the steps
of the central bank's announcement Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
