<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Wholesale Network Services Market to Expand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, December 14 (Xinhua) -- A report released Tuesday
projects that the U.S. wholesale network services market will grow
at an average annual rate of 24 percent in the next few years.
</P>
<P>
The market, driven primarily by Internet Protocol (IP) related
wholesale volume, is expected to reach 116 billion U.S. dollars in
revenue by 2003, up from 39 billion dollars in 1998, according to
the report from research and consulting firm Phillips Group.
</P>
<P>
The report said three key sectors account for increases in IP
related wholesale volumes.
</P>
<P>
The rapid growth of wireless wholesale services, driven by
Internet access, will jump from 500 million dollars in 1998 to 5.5
billion dollars in 2003, expanding 11 times.
</P>
<P>
The second biggest IP wholesale growth rate will be among new
entrants to the industry, known as competitive local exchange
carriers. These firms posted total wholesale revenues of 250
million dollars in 1998 and in five years, their revenues are
expected to multiply 10-fold, to 2.62 billion dollars in 2003.
</P>
<P>
Lastly, revenues of packet/cell-based network service providers,
which include the delivery of IP telephony, will jump from 2
billion dollars in 1998 to 20.4 billion dollars in 2003.
</P>
<P>
There are three key drivers in the U.S. wholesale network
service market, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The initial driver is the impact of ongoing deregulation of the
telecom environment and the growth in competition that it has
generated. The second driver has been the rapid acceleration of
telecom technologies, particularly fiber optic transmission and
switching capabilities that are resulting in the doubling of
bandwidth capabilities every nine months. The third driver has
been the impact of the Internet on the demand for bandwidth and
the transformation of bandwidth usage from circuit-switched voice
to IP packet networks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991215.0144 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
