<HEADLINE> China Holds Photo Exhibit on Life of 10th Panchen Lama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A photo exhibition depicting
the life of the 10th Panchen Lama Erdini Qoigyi Gyaincain opened
here at the Cultural Palace of the Nationalities here.
</P>
<P>
Panchen was born in Xunhua County of northwest China's Qinghai
Province in 1938. He was recognized as the reincarnation of the
9th Panchen Lama. He died in the Xigaze City of Tibet Autonomous
Region in 1989 at age 51.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the 10th anniversary of his death. The photo
exhibit, held by the China Photographers Association, was held to
honor "a great patriot and master religious leader," according to
the association.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 photos reflect Panchen's contribution to the
national unity and his work to improve the conditions for China's
ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
The pictures are the work of Liu Long, who had been working
with Panchen to record the historic events on film.
</P>
<P>
Ngapoi Ngawang Jigme, vice-chairman of the National Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
and Tomur Dawamat, Wang Guangying, both vice-chairmen of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC),
attended today's opening ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
