<HEADLINE> A Thai Bank to Render Foreign Employment Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's state-run Bank for
Agriculture and Agricultural Cooperatives (BAAC) will extend loans
to Thai citizens wishing to work overseas, Thailand News Agency
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
BAAC President Pitayapol Nath-tharadol was quoted as saying
that approved applicants would be given a maximum loan of 150,000
baht(3947 U.S. dollars) each with an annual interest rate of 10.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
The initiative, to be taken effect in January next year, was a
cooperative project between BAAC and the Ministry of Labor and
Social Welfare, he said.
</P>
<P>
Those applying for loans of no more than 90,000 baht (2368
dollars) would only pay an annual interest rate of 7.5 percent
while the rest of three percent would be shouldered by the
Ministry of Labor and Social Welfare.
</P>
<P>
Applicants of loans over 90,000 baht, however, would pay the
full interest rate of 10.5 percent only for the over-set-
privileged amount, Pitayapol said.
</P>
<P>
Borrowers could also make periodic repayments of their loans in
accordance with varied periods of their employment by overseas
firms, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
