<HEADLINE> S. Korea's Exports Hit 14.18 Billion U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Meanwhile, imports surged 40.8 percent to 11.73 billion dollars,
resulting in a trade surplus to 2.46 billion dollars in the said
month.
</P>
<P>
In the first 11 months of this year, the trade surplus amounted
to 21.6 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
South Korea had set this year's trade surplus target at 25
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
In November, telecom equipment and semiconductor items led the
strong exports while the higher oil prices were behind the sharp
increase of imports.
</P>
<P>
In addition, auto imports rocketed 1,108 percent last month and
those of golf products shot up 78.5 percent and clothing 137.8
percent. 
