<HEADLINE> Science and Technology Improve Navy's Combat Effectiveness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Navy has made
full use of science and technology in the improvement of its
combat effectiveness.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the Navy has emphasized the role of science
and technology in military drills and renovation, officials here
said.
</P>
<P>
The navy this year conducted dozens of difficult military
maneuvers, such as those designed to defend missile attacks, and
coordinated drills against submarine invasions and attacks by
hostile fleets.
</P>
<P>
Through the drills, the Navy has improved its combat
effectiveness in any circumstances, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the Navy explored new ways to closely link new
weapons research and military drills, thus making use of new
equipment.
</P>
<P>
It has also taken concrete measures to encourage technical
renovation, resulting in over 600 upgrades over the past few years.
</P>
