<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Expects Higher Growth in Overseas Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen City of south China'
s Guangdong Province expects a 20 percent growth in earnings from
its overseas tourism industry this year.
</P>
<P>
The city will rake in 1.05 billion U.S. dollars from hosting
overseas tourists in the year, information from the city tourism
bureau shows.
</P>
<P>
Chi Xiongbiao, deputy head of the bureau, said that the city
has double-digit growth in both the number of tourists and
earnings from tourism.
</P>
<P>
The city had well over 16 million overseas tourist arrivals
this year, said the official.
</P>
<P>
Tourism organizations of the city have taken pains to improve
tourism services in the city, including erecting consulting
services for tourism information at major public places,
distributing more free tourism brochures, and putting up tourist
information in both English and Chinese at major streets and bus
stops.  
</P>
