<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 11 Laws to Be Finalized in Macao Prior to Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Legislative Council of the
Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) will finish deliberating
and finalizing the 11 essential laws for the Macao SAR and one set
of principles governing the operations of the Legislative Council
by December 18, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The Macao SAR Legislative Council finished discussing and
finalizing the law governing the permanent Macao SAR residents and
the right of abode, and the Organic Law of Judicial System of
Macao at its plenary meeting on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The first 43 articles of the 115-article General Rules on Macao
Judges were also discussed and finalized at the Macao SAR
Legislative Council meeting on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Lau Cheok Va, vice-president of the Macao SAR Legislative
Council, said that they had long deliberations about two major
issues of the Organic Law of Judicial System of Macao, namely, the
vacation of the judges and the establishment of two offices.
</P>
<P>
The annual two-month vacation of Macao judges will be shortened
to one month after Macao's return in order to quicken the handling
of civil cases. Legislators also agreed to the establishment of
the offices of the procurator and of the president of the Court of
Final Appeal, which would be responsible for handling routine
affairs of the courts and procuratorate of Macao.
</P>
<P>
The deliberations about the General Rules on Macao Judges are
mainly centered on the part-time job of Macao judges, said Lau.
</P>
<P>
According to the Basic Law of the Macao SAR, a Macao SAR judge
shall not concurrently have a second job in any public or private
organizations nor shall have any job in political organizations
during his or her term of office.
</P>
<P>
Legislators held that if necessary, Macao judges may
concurrently take up a job as a law professor, undertake legal
training or research with the approval of the judges committee and
the procurator-general. 
</P>
</TEXT>
