<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Close Sharply Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks ended down
457.39 points, or 2.81 percent, to close at 15825.31 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover Wednesday was 11.74 billion HK dollars (1.5
billion U.S. dollars), 1.77 billion HK dollars (227 million U.S.
dollars) down from Tuesday's 13.51 billion HK dollars (1.73
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
All the four sub-indices saw losses, with Finance dropping by 1.
57 percent while Utilities, Properties and Commerce &AMP; Industry
lost 2.35 percent, 4.04 percent and 3.22 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index was down 2.02 percent and
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index down 1.75 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks were down 5.6 points, or 0.03 percent, to open
at 16,277.10 Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
