<HEADLINE> Romanian Weightlifting World Champion Tests Positive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Romanian gold medallist
Razvan Ilie tested positive for an anabolic steroid at last month'
s world weightlifting championships where he improved the world
snatch record, the Romanian Weightlifting Federation (FRH)
announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
FRH president and national team coach Nicu Vlad said: "Ilie
tested positive with methandienone and he was automatically banned,
" "If a second sample also tests positive, Ilie will have to
return the gold he got in Greece."
</P>
<P>
23-year-old Ilie was world snatch champion in the men's 77-kg
class in Athens. It is the second time he has tested positive
after a previous positive test in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
