<HEADLINE> Basic Construction Heavily Funded In E. China Towns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The investment used for
improving infrastructure in the towns of east China's Anhui
Province hit a record five billion yuan (600 million US dollars)
from January to September this year, a wide increase on a year-to-
year basis.
</P>
<P>
The province now has a total of 3,032 towns of varying sizes
inhabited by 11 million farmers and accounting for one-fifth of
province's rural population.
</P>
<P>
This year, the provincial government allocated 20 million yuan
(3.16 million US dollars) of discount-interest funds for the
construction of water supplies, roads and sanitation facilities in
these towns.
</P>
<P>
There are now 120 bigger towns in Anhui with a population above
20,000, 210 towns with a population ranging from 10,000 to 20,000,
and 310 smaller towns which cover areas greater than 20,000 square
kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
