<DOCNO> XIE19991215.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Creates National Science, Technology Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has
constituted a National Science and Technology Council to
coordinate, monitor and promote science and technology in the
country.
</P>
<P>
According to Wednesday's Zambia Daily Mail newspaper, the
existing barrier between the scientists and the residents has
contributed greatly to the economic degradation in the African
country.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Acting Technical Education and Vocational
Training Minister David Saviye as saying here on Tuesday that
there are abundant resources in the country but there is little
utilization of them.
</P>
<P>
He called on stakeholders to come up with a science
agenda-framework to address the socio-economic challenges
besetting the country.
</P>
<P>
To address the challenges, there is urgent need to reform the
current scientific and technological programs, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said stakeholders must re-examine the possibilities of
incorporating science into the policy-making process.
</P>
<P>
Saviye noted that science includes the improvement of
infrastructure like telecommunication facilities which have a
direct link on the utilization of local and foreign resources to
improve the economy.
</P>
<P>
Should these be improved by scientists and information imparted
to non- technical users, the country may attain the desired social
and economic development, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
