<HEADLINE> Chinese Refrigerator Earns Subsidy from German Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Officials with China's Haier
Group recently received a fax from their franchisers in Europe
saying that a consumer can get a government environmental subsidy
of 50 to 100 deutsche marks (30 to 60 U.S. dollars) when buying a
Haier refrigerator in Germany.
</P>
<P>
The fax said this is because Haier refrigerator have met the
highest standard of energy consumption in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The Haier Group, with headquarters in the scenic port city of
Qingdao in Shandong Province, east China, is the country's leading
producer of household electrical appliance. It has been making
freon-free and energy-saving refrigerators. In 1993, Haier
produced China's first completely freon-free refrigerator, which
also can save more than 40 percent of electricity use.
</P>
<P>
Haier refrigerators now sell well at the European market, which
is famous for its severe product requirements, and the group has
become the largest exporter of refrigerators to Germany. In the
United States, Hair has gained more than 20 percent of the market
of under-180-liter refrigerators.
</P>
<P>
Haier now sells products to some 80 countries and has set up
over 30,000 sales offices worldwide. In the first ten months of
this year, the company's total exports increased by 138 percent
over the same period of 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
