<HEADLINE> ITU Rejects Blood Testing Triathletes before Sydney Olympic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- International Triathlon Union
(ITU) President Les McDonald Wednesday rejected reports that the
ITU would conduct pioneering blood tests on athletes before event'
s at next year's Sydney Olympics, according to news from Melbourne.
</P>
<P>
Medical director of the International Olympic Committee Patrick
Schamasch last week said that international cycling and triathlon
federations had asked to carry out the tests and that other sports
were free to follow suit.
</P>
<P>
The ICU, cycling's world governing body, has already introduced
the blood tests and is expected to continue its program at the
Sydney Olympics, but McDonald said the ITU had no such plans.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview from his office in Vancouver, Canada,
McDonald told a foreign press in Melbourne: "Patrick contacted me
and said he was sorry triathlon had somehow been included in
sports that were prepared to do blood tests - it is not true."
</P>
</TEXT>
