<HEADLINE> Smooth Traffic Guaranteed During Macao's Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Smooth traffic is guaranteed
days around Macao's return to China on December 20, despite the
imposition of traffic restrictions in some areas, a local
transport official said.
</P>
<P>
Can Feng Li, sub-director of the Macao Land, Public Works and
Transport Service, told Xinhua today that Macao's transport
capacity can fully meet traffic needs despite the temporary
imposition of traffic restrictions in some sections of roads and
around areas adjacent to the venues for the ceremonies for the
handover and the establishment of the Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR) and relevant celebration activities.
</P>
<P>
Traffic restrictions are imposed on a larger area every year
during the annual Macao car racing, and yet Macao enjoys smooth
traffic, the official said, adding that there won't be large
numbers of vehicles coming into Macao around Macao's return.
</P>
<P>
More traffic lights have been added for the sake of the
upcoming celebration activities, he said, hoping local residents
would go to their nearby places on foot instead of driving cars on
December 19-21.
</P>
<P>
Macao has more than 50,000 vehicles, but has fewer traffic jams
than in Beijing and Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
