<HEADLINE> China Reports Stable Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Figures from the National
Bureau of Statistics (NBS) released today showed that fixed assets
investment increased by 5.9 percent last month to reach 236.2
billion yuan (28.4 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the industrial output and the retail sales were
rising smoothly, indicating a stable economic operation.
</P>
<P>
From January to November, the fixed assets investment totaled
1610.8 billion yuan, up 6.8 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Sales of consumer goods increased by 7.8 percent to reach 285.9
billion yuan in November.
</P>
<P>
In the month, the industrial sector completed 191.9 billion
yuan-worth of value-added output, enjoying a 7.6 percent of year-
on-year growth.
</P>
<P>
The economic efficiency of these firms was also improved. In
January-October period, the industrial firms as a whole registered
a net profit of 153.3 billion yuan, up 64.7 percent over the same
period of last year. The losses totaled 118.6 billion yuan, 12
percent less than last year.
</P>
<P>
But the consumer price index (CPI) and the retail price index (
RPI) continued to decline, said the NBS.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in November, the CPI decreased by 0.9
percent while the RPI went down 2.8 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
