<DOCNO> XIE19991215.0211 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Coal Bed Methane Structure Found in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese geologists said today
that they have found rich coal bed methane resources in an area of
1,700 square kilometers in southeastern Shanxi Province, north
China.
</P>
<P>
The proven reserve there is more than 47 billion cubic meters,
and the ultimate reserve may be more than 400 billion cubic meters,
according to the China National Petroleum Corporation.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest coal bed methane field ever found in China,
said an official with the corporation, which has been prospecting
for the gas resources in northern China in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Coal bed methane is a kind of clean energy that can be used for
cooking, power generation, and automobile fuel. It produces no
smog when burning, and its emissions of dioxide sulfur is lower
than that of coal.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, Chinese engineers dug the first experimental well in
Shanxi, which gushed 4,000 cubic meters of the gas a day, and five
more experimental wells were dug near the first well earlier this
year.
</P>
<P>
China has rich coal bed methane resources which can be utilized
as a new energy supplementing or replacing coal, petroleum, and
natural gas. Shanxi, one of the leading coal producers in China,
has one-seventh of the coal bed methane resources in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
