<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heavy Fog Affects No Flights at Beijing Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua)-- The heavy fog which covered
Beijing this morning didn't affect fights at the Capital
International Airport, according to sources with the airport.
</P>
<P>
"Take-offs and landings were not affected by the dense fog this
morning because the visibility in the air is up to the required
level-- higher than 700 meters," the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Heavy fog blanketed the capital early this morning, disrupting
normal traffic and causing some expressways to close temporarily.
</P>
<P>
But no major traffic accidents occurred during the period,
according to local police.
</P>
<P>
Beijing meteorologists attributed the dense fog to heavy
humidity in the air caused by the recent snow and low temperatures
over the past few days.
</P>
<P>
They said that all of north China was shrouded in the thick fog
this morning with visibility in some areas in Beijing falling to
one to two kilometers.
</P>
<P>
They predicted that the fog will be driven away this evening by
a cold front from the north. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
