<HEADLINE> Auto-Parts Exports See Sharp Rise in S. China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province in south
China exported 24.32 million U.S. dollars worth of auto parts from
January to November this year, a sharp rise of 30.2 percent on a
yearly basis, according to local customs statistics.
</P>
<P>
This increase is attributed to production expansion among local
auto-parts makers, and their efforts to increase their presence
overseas.
</P>
<P>
Exports include such items as wheels, clutches, brakes and
parts, as well as body-work parts, and other auto components.
</P>
<P>
More than 87 percent of local auto-parts exports go to Asia,
North America and Europe, and the rest to Africa, Latin America,
and Oceania.  
</P>
</TEXT>
