<HEADLINE> Merrill Lynch Expects Higher Global Economic Growth in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Merrill Lynch said Tuesday
that its research analysts expect the world economy of the year
2000 to feature accelerating growth, lower inflation and low
interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Economists at the financial management and advisory company
forecast global GDP growth at 3.3 percent for next year, above
consensus expectations, and up from an estimated 2.7 percent in
1999.
</P>
<P>
They believe that the U.S., Europe and Japan will be joined by
robust economic recovery in emerging markets, with Asia growing 6
percent and Latin America growing 3.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Across all markets, the company said in a report, technology,
communications and restructuring are the consistent investment
themes. 
</P>
