<HEADLINE> Zhuhai's Cruise Tours Around Macao Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Niyaz, a 64-year-old Moslem
from the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, northwest China, held
up his telescope to watch the high-rise buildings in Macao as he
cruised the strait by the piece of land that will return to the
motherland on December 20.
</P>
<P>
He was on a tour to the city of Zhuhai, accompanied by his
daughter, who works in the port city of Shenzhen in south China's
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
"It would be even more amazing to walk on the land of Macao,"
he said on the ferry cruising around the island as he clearly saw
the street scenes and clean and beautiful beaches.
</P>
<P>
The package tour organized by Zhuhai City has become a most
appealing activity for some one million tourists arriving in the
port city annually since the late 1980.
</P>
<P>
"Business was amazingly hot between January and September and
we expect it to peak this month," said Pan Xinglian, director of
the Zhuhai Tourist Administration.
</P>
<P>
Wu Cainan, chief executive at the Jiuzhou Tourist Agency, one
of the four franchised tourist firms offering loop tours around
Macao, said Macao's return to the motherland has brought
unprecedented opportunity to the company, as tourists, especially
those from the interior areas, have taken the tour round Macao in
record numbers.
</P>
<P>
The 40-minute tour sets off from Jiuzhou Port in Zhuhai, and
each ferry carries about 200 passengers, who usually crowd the
deck to take snapshots and point out the landmarks of Macao.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
