<HEADLINE> France Reaches America's Cup Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, December 15 (Xinhua) -- France qualified for the
America's Cup challenger round semi-finals in Auckland, New
Zealand, Wednesday after its opponent America True quiting race.
</P>
<P>
Since America True, which had already qualified, decided not
to race Monday it has been known that the Le defi francais
syndicate aboard 6 Sens would qualify. To get the points to make
it into the final six the French had to finish the cross line
alone.
</P>
<P>
That slammed the door on their nearest rival, Young America
from the New York Yacht Club, which was also sailing alone Monday
after Young Australia declined to race in the now pointless event.
</P>
<P>
It is not known yet whether 6 Sens and Young America will race
Thursday as they are scheduled to do so. The outcome is irrelevant
to the competition.
</P>
<P>
Eleven syndicates from seven countries began the competition
for the Louis Vuitton Cup which gives the winner the right to take
on Team New Zealand for the America's Cup in February.
</P>
<P>
The semi-finals begin on January 2 with each boat sailing each
other twice in a round robin.
</P>
<P>
The qualifiers are Italy's Prada Challenge, Japan's Nippon
Challenge, America True and America One, both from San Francisco,
Dennis Conner's Stars and Stripes from San Diego and France's Le
defi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
