<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Auto Sales in Thailand to Exceed 26-Month Record in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's automobile sales in
December are expected to exceed November's sales of 21,266 units,
a 26-month high, said a statement from Toyota Motor Thailand Ltd,
which is available Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Toyota, which made the Thai automobile industry statistics for
the government, said the December sales are very likely to break
the record because car companies usually stage sales campaigns
during the last month of the year.
</P>
<P>
Another indicator is the high number of orders auto firms
received at the motor show held in Bangkok from December 4 to 12.
</P>
<P>
Sales volume for the whole year of 1999 will most likely exceed
200,000 units, up by more than 40 percent from last year, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
Toyota predicted that the Thai auto market in 2000 would surge
to 260,000 to 280,000 units, rising by 30 to 40 percent from this
year.
</P>
<P>
However, the sales are still far off the 590,000 units that the
industry sold in 1996 before the financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
In November, some 21,266 new cars were sold in Thailand, an
increase of 16.07 percent from the previous month and a 59.1
percent surge from the same month a year ago.
</P>
<P>
For the first 11 month of this year, overall car market grew by
43.6 percent from the same period last year to a total of 181,134
units.
</P>
<P>
The one-ton pick-up truck segment recorded the highest growth
of 49.7 percent, totaling 106,293 units. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
