<DOCNO> XIE19991215.0246 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, US Cooperate on Coal Gasification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Texaco Development
Corporation of the United States, a noted producer of coal
gasification devices, recently sought cooperation in China by
authorizing a machine manufacturer to be "the qualified provider
of Texaco pressure vessels and spare parts."
</P>
<P>
The Jinzhou Heavy-Duty Machine Plant (JHDMP) in the city of
Dalian in northeastern Liaoning Province has become the first in
Asia licensed to produce coal gasification devices based on Texaco
technology.
</P>
<P>
Officials on both sides of the agreement are optimistic about
prospects for their cooperation because a centralized gas supply
is still not available in many small and medium-sized cities of
China, and these products will be greatly needed.
</P>
<P>
Practically pollution-free, gasification is thought to be an
ideal way to turn coal into gas, even though this process requires
sophisticated technologies.
</P>
<P>
Thus far, more than 10 enterprises have been equipped with
Texaco coal gasification devices produced by the JHDMP, whose
capacity to produce them has reached over a dozen units annually.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991215.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bad Loans in Thai Banks to Fall to 40 Pct by Year End </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to Bank of Thailand, the central bank, NPLs at the
end of October totaled 2.35 trillion baht (61 billion U.S. dollars)
, or 43.39 percent of the total outstanding loans.
</P>
<P>
NPLs accounting for four percent of the total outstanding loans
would be considered normal, according to Pisit.
</P>
<P>
Pisit said he is confident of a sharp fall of NPLs next year
due to improved economy, progress in debt restructuring and new
asset management companies set up by local institutions.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Thaioil, the country's largest oil refinery,
with debts totaling 2.25 billion dollars, won debt-restructuring
approval from its creditors.
</P>
<P>
Thai Farmers Bank has already announced plans to transfer some
80 billion baht (2.07 billion dollars) worth of bad loans to a new
asset management company run by GE capital and Goldman Sachs.
</P>
<P>
Regulators also plan to split bad loans at state-owned Krung
Thai Bank into a new asset management company, fully owned by the
central bank's Financial Institutions Development Fund.
</P>
<P>
Director of Siam Commercial Bank Olarn Chaipravat also expected
a sharp fall of bad loans due to massive loan write-offs.
</P>
<P>
He forecast that total loan write-offs by the end of this year
would total 334 billion baht (8.67 billion dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991215.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mass Organizations Promote Macao-Zhuhai Contacts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Mass organizations in Macao and
the city of Zhuhai in Guangdong Province, south China, are playing
a big role in promoting contacts and cooperation between the two
places.
</P>
<P>
Of Macao's 1,500 mass organizations, the Macao Federation of
Trade Unions is one of the most important non-governmental
organizations in the city.
</P>
<P>
The federation has maintained a very close relationship with
the Zhuhai Trade Union and often sends representatives to Zhuhai
for inspections, visits, and exchange programs.
</P>
<P>
The Zhuhai Trade Union has established a reception facility to
accommodate guests representing trade union organizations from
Hong Kong and Macao. By early this year, the Macao Federation of
Trade Unions had sent about 5,000 representatives to Zhuhai for
visits, sight-seeing tours, and academic exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Women's Federation has approximately 10,000 members,
and often organizes women's activities in the interior areas where
they see the astounding changes in the motherland, while inviting
women's organizations from the interior to visit Macao.
</P>
<P>
Contacts between the Zhuhai Women's Federation and related mass
organizations in Macao are diversified. Each year on March 8, the
International Women's Day, women in both Macao and Zhuhai attend
celebrations given by the other side.
</P>
<P>
On International Children's Day, gatherings and children's
calligraphy and painting shows are arranged to enhance friendship
among the youngsters of Macao and Zhuhai.
</P>
<P>
The Zhuhai Women's Federation also assign representatives to
help train kindergarten teachers for Macao. Kindergarten teachers
from both cities also visit the other and exchange experiences.
</P>
<P>
Mass organizations in Macao have also played a vital role in
financing construction projects and introducing business people
from overseas to invest or make donations for the construction of
public welfare facilities in Zhuhai.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991215.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, December 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italy is at the forefront of research and development
into alternative sources of energy and can rightly show the rest
of Europe the way forward, Italian industry Minister Pierluigi
Bersani said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a conference held by Enea, the national council for
nuclear and alternative energies, Bersani cited statistics showing
the steady development of alternative forms of energy in Italy
over the last ten years. (Italy-Energy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LOS ANGELES -- Standard &AMP; Poor's has revised its outlook for
the U.S. life insurance industry to negative from stable.
</P>
<P>
The global ratings service said that the revision reflects its
view that pressures affecting the industry and the industry's
attempts to confront those pressures over the next few years will
leave the industry weaker at the end of that period than it is
today.
</P>
<P>
According to the service's outlook report released Tuesday, the
overriding influence that will have a negative effect on ratings
will be the pressure on the industry by the capital markets to
attain greater efficiency in its deployment of capital. (US-Life
Insurance)
</P>
