<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Greatly Interested in Macao's Return to Motherland: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey conducted
among 2,500 residents in 10 major cities shows that the Chinese
people are highly interested in the return of Macao to the
Motherland on December 20.
</P>
<P>
All those polled said they will watch the live broadcast of the
return ceremony on the eve of return on December 19.
</P>
<P>
When stories about Macao appeared in the media, most of those
surveyed said they will read, watch, or listen carefully; 53.3
percent said they pay special attention, and only 9.9 percent said
they treat these stories like any other.
</P>
<P>
Eighty-five percent of those surveyed knew that Ho Hau Wah will
be the first chief executive of the Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR), and 11.7 percent said they knew very well about the
Basic Law of Macao SAR, while 38.6 percent consider themselves
knowledgeable about the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The survey also found that all those polled believe that Macao'
s return to the motherland is another big event following the
return of Hong Kong, and will end the era of foreign control of
Chinese territory.
</P>
<P>
All respondents said that the "One Country, Two Systems" policy
has been strictly observed and proved to be a success in Hong Kong,
and they have every confidence that the same will become true in
the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
Every one of those surveyed expressed their hope that the
Taiwan issue will soon be resolved and the country's reunification
realized.
</P>
<P>
The telephone survey was conducted by the Social Survey
Institute of China (SSIC) in Beijing, Tianjin, Shanghai, Guangzhou,
Shenzhen, Fuzhou and four other big cities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
