<HEADLINE> 705 Election-Related Incidents Reported in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With only six days more left for Sri Lanka's Presidential
election, all political parties here have called for a free and
fair election against the backdrop of such incidents of election
related violence, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Up to noon Tuesday, the ESPD had received 705 complaints of
such incidents, including four killings since November 9.
</P>
<P>
The other complaints covers attacks on party offices and
individuals, and harassment, intimidation and assault, the sources
said.
</P>
