<HEADLINE> Philippine Labor Force Increases by 2.3 Pct in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The labor force population of
the Philippines increased to 32 million in October, 2.3 percent
higher than the figure in the same month of 1998, an official
report said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The National Statistics Office said in its Labor Force Survey
that persons aged 15 years old and over reached 48.6 million in
October, an increase of 2.6 percent from 47.4 million in the same
month of 1998.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, employment persons in October
increased by 741,000 or 2.6 percent to 29 million from 28.3
million a year ago. Correspondingly, employment rate increased
from 90.4 percent to 90.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The increase in employment was absorbed mostly by the services
sector and employment in industry increased by 1.7 percent.
Employment in agriculture slightly increased by 0.6 percent in
October.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, unemployment persons decreased by 19,000 or
0.9 percent from 3 million last year. Unemployment rate also
decreased from 9.6 percent to 9.4 percent, said the report.
</P>
</TEXT>
