<HEADLINE> Chinese Exports Rise 32.4 Percent in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua)-- China imported and exported 36.
4 billion US dollars worth of goods in November, up 32.4 percent
over the same month last year and the highest growth rate this
year, according to the General Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
China's exports rose 28.8 percent to 19.5 billion US dollars
while imports grew 36.8 percent to 16.9 billion US dollars. The
country also had a trade surplus of 2.6 billion US dollars for the
month.
</P>
<P>
During the January-November period, total foreign trade volume
edged up by 12.7 percent to 323 billion US dollars. And China had
accumulated a trade surplus of 26.4 billion US dollars for the
year by the end of November. 
