<DOCNO> XIE19991215.0271 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Environment Protection Given Top Attention in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese residents are
developing an increasing awareness of their living environment as
a result of improved living standard.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays, people living in China's major metropolitans like
Beijing, Shanghai and Wuhan, would rather escape the smog-shrouded
downtown area and move to the suburbs for better air quality.
Environmental topics have become as popular as talking about the
weather. School children now are quite familiar with such terms as
air pollution index, water resources, noise pollution, and air-
infectious bacteria.
</P>
<P>
The public attention given to the environment has boosted
intensified scientific research efforts to reduce urban pollution.
Research fellows at the South China Institute of Forestry are
concentrating on the study of environmentally friendly plants.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yong'an, a professor with the China Forestry
Administration, predicts that public attention to environmental
protection will continue to grow.
</P>
<P>
Government officials and experts from heavily polluted cities
such as Beijing, Shanghai, Chongqing and Shenyang, recently
convened a meeting in Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei
Province, to discuss ways of promoting sustainable development
while protecting the environment.
</P>
<P>
A soaring number of vehicles on the roads and the growing
population have produced heavy burdens, exacerbating pollution in
these cities. Participants at the meeting agreed that priority
should be given to treating air pollution, residential garbage,
and traffic congestion.
</P>
<P>
China has designated 34 zones as experimental areas for
sustainable development in China's cities, and they have been
allowed to introduce foreign management methods and capital for
urban constructopm. International cooperation will also contribute
to these efforts, as Wuhan and Shenyang have been enlisted in a
United Nations sustainable development program aimed at
alleviating pollution through proper planning.
</P>
<P>
Now, China's environmental regulators have sketched out a
series of procedures to treat pollution under a national
ecological investment program of the State Planning Commission,
the "Green Illuminating Project" under the State Economic and
Trade Commission, and regulations on controlling sulfur dioxide
and acid rain promulgated by the State Environmental Protection
Administration.
</P>
<P>
However, the fundamental solution to problems of environmental
protection lies in overall ecological recovery, according to
ecologists. This task has been made more urgent by the
unprecedented floods on the Yangtze, China's longest river, in the
past two years, which are blamed for serious soil erosion along
the upper reaches of the river.
</P>
<P>
A greening project initiated by the State Forestry
Administration and the Ministry of Water Resources has helped
expand greenery over some 6.29 million hectares, and banned
logging on 1.26 million hectares along the river over the past
seven years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
