<HEADLINE> Large Copper Market Built in Anhui </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A state-level copper market,
covering an area of 28,000 square meters, has been built in the
city of Tongling in east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
The total investment for the market reached more than 70
million yuan (8.4 million US dollars), a local source said.
</P>
<P>
Tongling is the largest producer of copper in east China. It
has been producing copper for more than 3,000 years, and now turns
out about half of country's total copper goods annually.
</P>
<P>
The market intends to become a national distribution center for
copper commodities, officials said, adding that it will promote
economic and technological exchange and cooperation among copper
producers and traders, and accelerate the development of the
copper industry. 
