<HEADLINE> Bus-Truck Collision Kills 28 in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 14 (Xinhua) -- A head-on collision
between a bus and a gas tank truck killed 28 people and injured 16
others in the central Mexican state of Guanajuato, the country's
Federal Highway Police (PFC) said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place Monday on the highway between
Salvatierra and Celaya of the state, 233 kilometers northwest of
the Mexican capital, said a PFC spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The two vehicles, both running at a high speed, collided when
invading each other's lane.
</P>
<P>
The two drivers and many of the passengers on board the bus
were killed. Damage of the accident was estimated around 107,500 U.
S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
It was not reported whether the truck was then loaded with gas.
No explosion occurred the moment the collision happened. 
</P>
