<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jailed Nazi War Criminal Suffers Heart Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Ex-SS captain Erich Priebke, 85,
who is serving a life sentence in Rome as a war criminal, suffered
a heart attack Tuesday and was taken to hospital, his attorney
Paolo Giachini said.
</P>
<P>
Priebke, who was serving his jail term under house arrest at
Giachini's home, was accompanied by the attorney to San Camillo
Hospital in Rome, according to the ANSA news agency.
</P>
<P>
Priebke arrived at the hospital late in the afternoon,
complaining of strong pains in his left chest. Doctors said they
would keep him under observation for 24 hours before deciding on
treatment.
</P>
<P>
ANSA said Priebke's room in the hospital is under guard by
Carabinieri, Italy's paramilitary police.
</P>
<P>
Priebke was convicted for his part in the brutal 1944 massacre
of 335 Italian men and boys at the Ardeatine Caves on the
outskirts of Rome in reprisal for the killing of 32 German
soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Priebke's provisional first year of house arrest will end on
February 8. If it is not renewed, he will have to go back to jail.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
