<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Jolts Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 14 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.
5 on the Richter scale jolted the Mexican capital and the southern
state of Oaxaca Tuesday, but no damage was reported.
</P>
<P>
The National Seismological Service reported that the moderate
quake hit the two areas at 01:11 am (local time) and was centered
in the continental mass between the adjoining states of Guerrro
and Oaxaca, both along the Pacific Ocean.
</P>
<P>
Many residents rushed out of their homes for fear of collapse
in the Pinotepa de Don Luis municipality in Oaxaca, where the
quake was felt more strongly, local authorities said.
</P>
<P>
Civil Protection authorities said that the seism did not cause
any damage.
</P>
<P>
A quake measuring 7.4 on the Richter scale rocked Oaxaca on
September 30, killing 27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
