<HEADLINE> Norway Qualifies for Ice Hockey World Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Sweden-based Espen Knutsen
Tuesday scored one goal and set up another to inspire Norway to
beat England 2-1 in a play-off match and qualified for next year's
ice hockey world championship finals (Group A) in the Dutch city
Eindhoven.
</P>
<P>
Knutsen, playing for Swedish first division team Dju Rgaarden,
broke the deadlock with nine seconds remaining in the first period
and feeded his teammate Petter Salsten with a superb cross for the
latter to settle the matters ten minutes into the second period.
</P>
<P>
England replied six minutes later with a consolation goal,
which proved to be too little and too late.
</P>
<P>
Norway failed to qualify directly from this May's world
championship where it had home advantage but only ended up 12th on
the standings. Norway also missed out in the qualifying tournament
in France and had to make it hard way through a play-off match.
</P>
<P>
The 2000 world championship, scheduled in Russia next spring,
will have Norway in the third Group with defending champion Czech
Republic, Canada and Japan. 
</P>
